Chidiebube Okeoma, Owerri Personnel of the Orji Police Division in Imo State have arrested three robbery suspects, who operated in the area. Our correspondent learnt that the suspects were arrested at Akwakuma in Owerri, the state capital. A source in the area said that the Divisional Police Officer, SP Chisom Ezebuiro, led the operation that led to the arrest of the suspects. The source gave the names of the suspects as Uzochukwu Onyenwenyi, 29, from Akwakuma; Nnaeme Elendu, 29, from Anambra State; and Marvellous  Ekezie, 24, from Amaifeke Orlu, Imo State. The source said, “A case of armed robbery took place at Akwakuma. Three men of the underworld took part in the dangerous operation. “A Mercedes Benz 4matic, jewellery worth hundreds of thousands of naira, N300,000 cash, eight sophisticated phones, one generator, two television sets and other items were taken away during the operation. “One of the prime suspects was arrested five days ago and he confessed to the crime, which led to the arrest of the remaining two suspects. Their arms and vehicle have been recovered. Some of the phones have also been recovered.” The outgoing Commissioner of Police in the state, Rabiu Ladodo, confirmed the breakthrough. Copyright PUNCH.
